---
import GeneratorLayout from "../layouts/GeneratorLayout.astro";
---

<GeneratorLayout
    title="About zygote.ro"
    description="Learn about zygote.ro, the developer generator hub designed to help you bootstrap projects instantly."
>
    <div class="content-limit">
        <h1>About zygote.ro</h1>

        <div class="prose">
            <p class="intro">
                <strong>zygote.ro</strong> is a collection of free, high-quality code
                generators designed to help developers stop writing boilerplate and
                start building features.
            </p>

            <h2>The Concept</h2>
            <p>
                In biology, a <em>zygote</em> is the very first state of a new unique
                organism before it begins to divide and grow. Similarly, our tools
                help you generate the "zygote" of your projectâ€”the perfect, healthy
                starting point from which your software can grow.
            </p>

            <h2>Our Mission</h2>
            <p>
                Software development should be about unique value, not
                repetitive configuration. We aim to provide:
            </p>
            <ul>
                <li>
                    <strong>Zero boilerplate</strong>: Get the files you need
                    instantly.
                </li>
                <li>
                    <strong>Best practices</strong>: Generated code follows
                    modern standards.
                </li>
                <li>
                    <strong>Privacy first</strong>: All generation happens in
                    your browser. No data is sent to our servers.
                </li>
            </ul>

            <h2>Tech Stack</h2>
            <p>
                zygote.ro is built with performance and sustainability in mind:
            </p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Astro</strong>: For blazing fast static pages.</li>
                <li><strong>TypeScript</strong>: For type-safe reliability.</li>
                <li>
                    <strong>Vanilla CSS</strong>: For lightweight, future-proof
                    styling.
                </li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </div>
</GeneratorLayout>

<style>
    .content-limit {
        max-width: 800px;
        margin: 0 auto;
    }

    h1 {
        font-size: 2.5rem;
        font-weight: 800;
        margin-bottom: 2rem;
        color: var(--color-text);
    }

    h2 {
        font-size: 1.5rem;
        font-weight: 700;
        margin-top: 2.5rem;
        margin-bottom: 1rem;
        color: var(--color-text);
    }

    .prose p {
        font-size: 1.125rem;
        line-height: 1.8;
        color: var(--color-muted-foreground);
        margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    }

    .intro {
        font-size: 1.25rem;
        color: var(--color-text) !important;
    }

    ul {
        margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
        padding-left: 1.5rem;
    }

    li {
        font-size: 1.125rem;
        line-height: 1.8;
        color: var(--color-muted-foreground);
        margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
    }

    strong {
        color: var(--color-text);
        font-weight: 600;
    }
</style>
